This article summarizes remarks made by President Trump during a meeting with Navajo Code Talkers, who played a crucial role in World War II. The Code Talkers were recruited by the Marine Corps to use the Navajo language as a secret code that the enemy could not decipher. The President praised their bravery and expressed his gratitude for their service. He also mentioned his support for the creation of a national Navajo Code Talker Museum. The President then briefly discussed the progress of the tax bill, stating that it will be the biggest tax reduction in US history and will benefit everyone, particularly those looking for jobs.